# Rule routing map

[`index.mdc`](index.mdc) is the **project constitution** (always active). Other rules use `globs` when matching files are open; for multi-domain work, treat every matching rule as active.

## When to apply each rule

| You are working on | Activate |
|--------------------|----------|
| Project-wide identity, stack, storage invariants | `index.mdc` (always) |
| Agent efficiency, verified facts, concise communication | `index.mdc` (Agent efficiency and accuracy) |
| TypeScript, Zustand, WatermelonDB/MMKV usage, performance | `technical-excellence.mdc` |
| Screens, layout, styling, motion, design tokens | `ui-ux-design.mdc` |
| WatermelonDB models, migrations, MMKV keys, stores vs DB | `data-layer.mdc` |
| Vision Camera, FFmpeg, file paths, cache vs document | `media-processing.mdc` |
| Streaks, notifications tone, AI companion UX, empathy | `behavioral-psychology.mdc` |
| Notifee channels, triggers, payloads, handlers, reschedule/cancel semantics | `notification-system.mdc` |

## Skills

Project skills live in `.cursor/skills/{name}/SKILL.md`. Read the matching skill when the trigger applies.

| Skill | Trigger |
|-------|---------|
| `add-i18n-key` | Any user-visible string is added or changed |
| `add-screen` | New React Navigation screen (stack, tab, modal) |
| `add-domain-feature` | Feature work under `src/features/*` (journal, streak, capsule, etc.) |
| `add-watermelondb-model` | New table, model class, or WatermelonDB migration |
| `add-notification` | Notifee channels, triggers, foreground/initial handlers, i18n copy, or notification-related native permission config |
| `subscription-gate` | Free vs Pro limits, paywall, `can*` helpers |
| `add-ai-feature` | OpenAI / Whisper / GPT integration or prompts |

## Maintenance contract

**New rule:** add `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` with a tight `globs` pattern, then add a row to the table above. **New skill:** add `.cursor/skills/{name}/SKILL.md`, then add a row here. Do not broaden existing `globs` — prefer narrow patterns and this table for orientation.
